  "article_text": "Welcome to the Star Atlas weekly recap from the Intergalactic Herald. Below is what happened with Star Atlas this past week.\nWe are looking for guests to be on our podcast. The podcast is a discussion of the past week’s news about Star Atlas. If you are interested in being on the podcast, please contact us.\nWe are launching a Star Atlas merch store. Please check it out at Intergalactic Gear.\nWe are creating a “non-guild” guild. If you are interested in learning more, please go to Intergalactic Coalition.\nIf you would like to support our efforts, donations can be sent to intergalacticherald.sol\nMichael Wagner – Development and Challenges of Star Atlas\nAephia posted a video interview with Star Atlas CEO Michael Wagner by the MetaVerse Explorer.\nWhy Star Atlas token prices are sinking despite bull run\nSiggy published an article talking about the price of the ATLAS token.\nMetaverse Nomads #156 Three Year Anniversary\nMetaverse Nomads posted a video of their weekly Star Atlas livestream.\nHow to play Starbased as a small player\nAephia posted a video about how to play Starbased as a small player.\nWeekly Star Atlas Newsletter #139\nAephia published their weekly Star Atlas newsletter.\nAephia Content Overview\nAephia posted a video about content they have created.\nStar Atlas DAO passes first two governance proposals\nHologram News Network published an article about the Star Atlas DAO proposals.\nSTAR ATLAS #244 Happy 3rd Anniversary To All Aephians!\nMetaVerse Explorer posted a video of Star Atlas updates.\nThe Atlas Brew #121\nStar Atlas TV posted a video recording of the latest Atlas Brew.\nCrew Packs and Star Atlas Airdrops are Coming in August — Important Dates, Utility in SAGE Labs, and More!\nStar Atlas published an article about the release of Star Atlas Crew Packs.\nStar Atlas sponsors Solana hackathon with $50,000 in prizes\nHologram News Network published an article about a Star Atlas hackathon.\nBecome Part of the Universe | Crew Packs Trailer – Star Atlas\nStar Atlas posted a video trailer about Crew Packs.\nStarbased – The Missing Manual – Part 2\nAephia published a second part of a missing manual for Star Atlas SAGE Starbased.\nStar Atlas Brew #121: State of the Community – TLDR\nBeth posted a video recapping the latest Atlas Brew.",
